  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Manager",
  "description": "<h2>Key Responsibilities</h2><ul><li><p>Overall planning, execution, monitoring, and completion of construction projects</p></li><li><p>Manage project schedule, cost control, quality, and safety performance</p></li><li><p>Liaise with consultants, subcontractors, suppliers, and clients</p></li><li><p>Prepare and monitor master programme, project budgets, progress claims, and variation orders</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with BCA, MOM, NEA, LTA (if appliable), and statutory requirements</p></li><li><p>Lead site teams including engineers, supervisors, and subcontractors</p></li><li><p>Identify risks and implement mitigation measures</p></li><li><p>Chair project meetings and prepare progress reports</p></li><li><p>Ensure works are carried out in accordance with drawings, specifications, and contract requirements</p></li></ul><h2>Requirements / Qualifications</h2><p><p>Degree in Civil Engineering, Building, Construction Management, or related field<br /><br />Singaporean/PR</p></p><p><p>Minimum 5–10 years of relevant construction experience (adjust as needed)</p></p><p><p>Proven experience as Project Manager for building or civil projects</p></p><p><p>Strong knowledge of construction methods, contracts, and local regulations</p></p><p><p>Familiar with Singapore construction standards and authorities’ submissions</p></p><p><p>Able to manage multiple stakeholders and tight project timelines</p></p><p><p>Strong leadership, communication, and problem-solving skills</p></p><p>Proficient in MS Office and project management tools (e.g. MS Project / Primavera)1) Minimum 5 years experience in managing construction projects on site<br /><br />Understand PSSCOC and SIA contracts</p><p><br /></p><p></p>",
